		templ_7745c5c3_Err = templruntime.WriteString(templ_7745c5c3_Buffer, 18, "\"><p class=\"text-sm text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-300 mb-5\">Stillwater manages artist metadata and images for your self-hosted music library. It writes NFO files and organizes artwork so your media server displays rich artist information.</p><div class=\"grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 gap-3\"><div class=\"rounded-lg border border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700 p-3\"><h3 class=\"text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900 dark:text-gray-100 mb-1\">Metadata (NFO Files)</h3><p class=\"text-xs text-gray-500 dark:text-gray-400\">Fetch biographies, genres, styles, moods, and formation dates from multiple sources and write them as standard NFO files your media server can read.</p></div><div class=\"rounded-lg border border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700 p-3\"><h3 class=\"text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900 dark:text-gray-100 mb-1\">Image Management</h3><p class=\"text-xs text-gray-500 dark:text-gray-400\">Download and manage artist thumbnails, fanart, logos, and banners. Compare options side-by-side, crop to fit, and save in the correct format for your platform.</p></div><div class=\"rounded-lg border border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700 p-3\"><h3 class=\"text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900 dark:text-gray-100 mb-1\">Provider System</h3><p class=\"text-xs text-gray-500 dark:text-gray-400\">Pull data from MusicBrainz, Fanart.tv, TheAudioDB, Last.fm, Discogs, Wikidata, and Deezer. Configure priority order per field so the best source wins.</p></div><div class=\"rounded-lg border border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700 p-3\"><h3 class=\"text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900 dark:text-gray-100 mb-1\">Platform Profiles</h3><p class=\"text-xs text-gray-500 dark:text-gray-400\">Choose your media server (Emby, Jellyfin, or Kodi) and Stillwater adapts NFO format and image naming conventions to match what it expects.</p></div><div class=\"rounded-lg border border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700 p-3\"><h3 class=\"text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900 dark:text-gray-100 mb-1\">Rule Engine</h3><p class=\"text-xs text-gray-500 dark:text-gray-400\">Define rules that automatically apply metadata decisions across your library. Set genre mappings, image preferences, and field overrides that run on every fetch.</p></div><div class=\"rounded-lg border border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700 p-3\"><h3 class=\"text-sm font-semibold text-gray-900 dark:text-gray-100 mb-1\">Scanner Exclusions</h3><p class=\"text-xs text-gray-500 dark:text-gray-400\">Directories named \"Various Artists\", \"VA\", \"Soundtrack\", or \"OST\" are excluded from scanning by default. These compilation folders lack meaningful artist metadata.</p></div></div></div><!-- Step 1: Music Libraries -->")
